  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-31431:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\ncrypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place\n\nTo mitigate this issue, we recommend that customers disable loading of the algif_aead module by running the following commands:\n\n    echo \"install algif_aead /bin/false\" \u003e /etc/modprobe.d/disable-algif.conf\n\n    rmmod algif_aead 2\u003e/dev/null || true\n\nThis issue requires local authenticated access as a prerequisite; remote unauthenticated activity is not possible.\n",
